WEBVTT

00:33.930 --> 00:35.759
[Sighs]

00:42.352 --> 00:44.285
[Door opens]

00:49.325 --> 00:50.671
- Hi, Sarah?
- Yes.

00:50.705 --> 00:52.190
Hi, I'm Claire.
Nice to meet you.

00:52.224 --> 00:54.468
- Nice to meet you.
- Right this way.

01:01.613 --> 01:03.511
So, what's the plan?

01:03.546 --> 01:07.308
I need a color touch-up,
as you can see, and a trim.

01:08.275 --> 01:10.484
OK, sounds good.

01:10.518 --> 01:13.383
Can I get you something
to drink? Water, wine?

01:13.418 --> 01:16.455
Oh, my gosh,
a glass of wine sounds amazing.

01:16.490 --> 01:17.698
Yes, red.

01:17.732 --> 01:19.734
I'll be right back with that
and the color.

01:32.161 --> 01:33.645
[Pouring wine]

01:40.893 --> 01:42.654
- Here you go.
- Oh, thank you.

01:42.688 --> 01:44.138
Mm.

01:49.799 --> 01:51.766
So, are you in town for work?

01:53.527 --> 01:54.838
Yeah, um...

01:54.873 --> 01:58.394
Is it that obvious
I'm not from around here?

01:58.428 --> 02:00.465
Uh... no.

02:07.920 --> 02:09.474
Do you travel a lot for work?

02:09.508 --> 02:10.785
Yeah.

02:11.579 --> 02:13.616
Must be exciting.

02:13.650 --> 02:16.722
It's not as luxurious
as it seems.

02:17.758 --> 02:19.691
And I miss my family.

02:19.725 --> 02:21.417
Family?

02:21.451 --> 02:23.660
Yep. Husband
and a 12-year-old.

02:24.730 --> 02:26.215
Sweet.

02:28.320 --> 02:30.598
Sometimes I wonder
if I hate being gone so much

02:30.633 --> 02:33.532
because...
he seems so fine with it.

02:33.567 --> 02:34.671
I'm obsolete.

02:34.706 --> 02:37.295
I'm sure that's not true.

02:37.329 --> 02:38.710
Moms are moms.

02:39.987 --> 02:42.714
I guess,
even when we can't be.

02:48.996 --> 02:50.653
What do you do?

02:50.687 --> 02:52.620
Graphic design.

02:52.655 --> 02:54.450
Really?

02:54.484 --> 02:57.418
Didn't think that was a job
you had to travel for.

02:57.453 --> 02:59.834
Seems like a job
you could just do at home.

03:02.665 --> 03:05.875
But I don't know anything
about it, though, really.

03:08.360 --> 03:11.467
Well, you mostly can.

03:11.501 --> 03:15.298
But I prefer to meet
bigger clients face-to-face.

03:16.057 --> 03:17.576
You make a better connection

03:17.611 --> 03:19.682
when you can look them
in the eye.

03:24.825 --> 03:26.792
I wish my hair would do that.

03:28.415 --> 03:30.451
But we all want
what we don't have.

03:31.418 --> 03:33.005
That's certainly true.

03:33.040 --> 03:35.456
- [Phone rings]
- Oh, um...

03:35.491 --> 03:37.044
Do you mind if I get this?
It's my husband.

03:37.078 --> 03:38.666
Not at all.

03:38.701 --> 03:40.323
Hey babe, what's up?

03:41.290 --> 03:43.878
How's David?

03:43.913 --> 03:45.673
Well, you can tell him
I'll be home this weekend,

03:45.708 --> 03:46.778
and it better be done by then.

03:46.812 --> 03:48.780
[Woman] Have a good night,
Claire.

03:48.814 --> 03:51.679
OK, talk to you tomorrow.
Love you, too. Bye.

03:55.580 --> 03:58.479
Am I keeping you late?
I feel bad.

03:58.514 --> 03:59.722
Oh, no.

03:59.756 --> 04:01.724
I work late most week nights.

04:01.758 --> 04:04.520
It seems to be
my most valuable time.

04:07.937 --> 04:11.492
- [Phone beeps]
- Oh, uh... sorry, I, uh...

04:11.527 --> 04:13.529
Well, I met a boy toy here
this week,

04:13.563 --> 04:15.841
and now he won't leave me alone.

04:15.876 --> 04:18.844
- [Phone beeps]
- Yeah?

04:18.879 --> 04:21.088
I'm only human, you know?

04:21.122 --> 04:22.917
It gets lonely.

04:22.952 --> 04:24.850
And even at home
we haven't had sex since...

04:24.885 --> 04:26.818
Are you liking Kansas City?

04:27.646 --> 04:28.958
Oh...

04:29.821 --> 04:31.029
Yeah, uh...

04:31.063 --> 04:32.755
Don't get me wrong,

04:32.789 --> 04:34.791
I love traveling, I...

04:34.826 --> 04:37.587
I love constantly meeting
new people, it's so inspiring.

04:37.622 --> 04:38.657
Yeah.

04:39.796 --> 04:41.488
That's why I do hair.

04:42.696 --> 04:45.423
- Really?
- Yeah.

04:45.457 --> 04:48.322
You get to go in and out
of people's lives,

04:48.357 --> 04:51.567
you hear stories,
you give life advice.

04:52.637 --> 04:54.915
It's almost like
having a family.

04:56.019 --> 04:57.987
Family...

04:58.021 --> 04:59.816
You know something?

04:59.851 --> 05:02.923
I have a sister,
I have two best friends at home,

05:02.957 --> 05:04.683
I even have a therapist,

05:04.718 --> 05:07.617
and the only two people
who know I'm cheating on Greg...

05:07.652 --> 05:09.067
are Boy Toy and you.

05:10.482 --> 05:11.725
Why?

05:11.759 --> 05:13.520
You trust me?

05:13.554 --> 05:15.142
You're a total stranger.

05:15.176 --> 05:19.733
You're... You're outside
my actual real life.

05:19.767 --> 05:22.805
With you, I...
I trust that it doesn't matter.

05:22.839 --> 05:24.945
I trust I'll never
see you again

05:24.979 --> 05:28.673
and my secret just...
vanishes with you.

11:06.424 --> 11:08.150
Hi, Pepper!

11:08.184 --> 11:09.876
How's my girl?

12:44.039 --> 12:45.247
[Sniffs]

12:47.905 --> 12:49.769
[Breathes heavily]

13:09.340 --> 13:11.480
[Sobbing]

14:01.150 --> 14:03.843
I guess we all want
what we don't have.

14:32.423 --> 14:34.425
[Chuckles]

14:53.306 --> 14:55.411
[Phone buzzes]

15:08.045 --> 15:09.909
[Water running]

16:16.561 --> 16:18.736
Are you ever gonna use it?

16:20.669 --> 16:23.189
No, and I told you that
when you bought it for me.

16:23.223 --> 16:26.192
- It's safer.
- Safer than what? Sunshine?

16:26.226 --> 16:27.745
Safer than going alone.

16:27.779 --> 16:30.782
I wouldn't be alone
if you would come with me.

16:30.817 --> 16:32.232
I'm going to take a shower.

16:32.267 --> 16:34.200
I might be gone
by the time you get done.

16:34.234 --> 16:37.444
Well, be careful,
I hear it's dangerous out there.

16:40.102 --> 16:42.173
- [Woman] There you go.
- [Man] Thanks.

16:42.208 --> 16:43.416
Hi.

16:43.450 --> 16:45.245
Hi, what can I get for you?

16:45.280 --> 16:46.798
Can I get a cappuccino, please?

16:46.833 --> 16:49.594
- Yeah, for sure. What size?
- Small.

16:49.629 --> 16:51.217
- Anything else for you?
- No.

16:51.251 --> 16:53.046
Alright.

17:05.817 --> 17:07.681
[Distorted] I'll have that
right out for you.

17:07.716 --> 17:09.200
Thank you.

17:09.235 --> 17:12.272
Medium almond milk chai latte?

17:13.825 --> 17:15.448
Uh...

17:16.311 --> 17:17.346
Claire?

17:20.418 --> 17:22.351
- Want your usual?
- Um...

17:22.386 --> 17:27.253
Chai latte with almond milk,
please.

17:27.287 --> 17:30.290
OK, so your usual.
Um... medium?

17:31.912 --> 17:33.707
- Small is fine.
- OK.

17:37.918 --> 17:39.644
Thanks.

18:00.458 --> 18:01.666
Claire?

18:01.701 --> 18:04.497
That chai for you
that you clearly need.

18:05.843 --> 18:07.155
Thanks.

18:07.948 --> 18:09.433
See you.

19:29.892 --> 19:32.481
Hey, yeah, it's Olivia.
What the fuck?

19:33.482 --> 19:34.828
I get that,

19:34.863 --> 19:36.899
but look in the lower
left-hand corner.

19:36.934 --> 19:39.005
You see where it says
"cuticle management"?

19:39.039 --> 19:42.802
Yeah, this is in fact an ad
for cubicles, not cuticles.

19:42.836 --> 19:44.355
Yeah, it's a problem.

19:45.977 --> 19:47.669
OK, great.

19:47.703 --> 19:49.395
Thank you.

19:54.676 --> 19:57.506
Is it too soon
to say I'm sorry?

19:57.541 --> 19:59.681
- Yeah.
- I heard about Natalie bailing.

19:59.715 --> 20:02.235
She's always been
really reliable, I swear.

20:02.270 --> 20:04.720
It's OK, it's not your fault.
Don't worry about it.

20:04.755 --> 20:06.515
So, what are you going to do?

20:06.550 --> 20:09.277
I texted my regular stylist
this morning.

20:09.311 --> 20:10.761
She doesn't normally
do weddings,

20:10.795 --> 20:13.764
but I begged and hopefully
I'll hear back later today.

20:13.798 --> 20:16.007
- She any good?
- She is amazing.

20:16.042 --> 20:17.492
She was my first choice.

20:17.526 --> 20:20.495
The stuff she does with hair -
jaw-dropping.

20:20.529 --> 20:22.842
Well, if she's so good,
why doesn't she do weddings?

20:22.876 --> 20:25.603
That's a good question.

20:25.638 --> 20:28.503
I think they're a little
high stress for her.

20:29.400 --> 20:30.436
Hmm!

20:55.944 --> 20:58.395
Aren't you worried
about fitting in your dress?

20:58.429 --> 20:59.810
At this rate,
I'll be walking down the aisle

20:59.844 --> 21:02.847
in a baseball cap and overalls,
so I need this.

21:03.814 --> 21:05.712
Is everything else going OK?

21:06.989 --> 21:08.784
As smoothly as possible.

21:08.819 --> 21:10.545
Charlie is a little tense,

21:10.579 --> 21:13.064
but we haven't hired
assassins yet.

21:13.099 --> 21:15.515
Well, if you ever need
a recommendation,

21:15.550 --> 21:16.758
I might know someone.

21:17.483 --> 21:18.587
Oh, really?

21:18.622 --> 21:20.313
Cos your hair lady
just bailed on me,

21:20.348 --> 21:22.073
so what do I do
if your hit man bails on me?

21:22.108 --> 21:23.661
I'd be totally fucked.

22:14.402 --> 22:15.851
[Phone beeps]

22:40.428 --> 22:42.395
Hi Dawn, the usual.

22:42.430 --> 22:44.639
Oh, there's the Claire I know.

22:44.673 --> 22:46.503
You doing better today?

22:46.537 --> 22:47.642
- Great.
- Good.

22:47.676 --> 22:50.092
Everything's great.

22:50.127 --> 22:52.957
- Thank you.
- Hi.

23:11.493 --> 23:13.978
[Door opens]

23:14.013 --> 23:17.016
Hi.
Come on back.

23:17.050 --> 23:20.951
Claire, you are literally
saving my life.

23:20.985 --> 23:22.884
I don't know about all that.

23:22.918 --> 23:25.749
So, tell me everything.

23:25.783 --> 23:27.198
- Oh, could you take this off?
- Oh.

23:29.200 --> 23:31.030
What are you hoping for?

23:31.064 --> 23:32.997
Do you have pictures
of your dress?

23:33.032 --> 23:35.034
Do I have pictures
of the dress!

23:36.484 --> 23:37.554
OK.

23:39.590 --> 23:43.732
Oh, my God,
you look amazing.

23:43.767 --> 23:46.908
Yeah? It's the first one
I tried on.

23:47.495 --> 23:49.048
Amazing.

23:49.082 --> 23:50.498
Perfect.

23:50.532 --> 23:54.087
Alright, so hair,
what are you hoping for?

23:54.122 --> 23:56.676
I mean, with that dress
you could really wear any style.

23:56.711 --> 24:01.923
Yeah, so, like...
down and a little curly.

24:01.957 --> 24:04.270
Do you have any photos of, like,
the styles you like,

24:04.304 --> 24:05.858
so I can kind of
have an idea?

24:05.892 --> 24:09.240
Yeah, I took your advice,
I did a lot of research.

24:10.725 --> 24:12.623
- Like this.
- OK.

24:13.866 --> 24:15.212
I love it.

24:20.562 --> 24:24.117
So, how is Charlie handling
the wedding madness?

24:24.152 --> 24:26.292
Is he excited?

24:26.326 --> 24:27.983
Yeah, I mean,
way more than me.

24:29.157 --> 24:31.539
He loves being the center
of attention.

24:31.573 --> 24:33.161
We should all probably
be worried

24:33.195 --> 24:34.990
that he's going to turn
into a groom-zilla.

24:35.025 --> 24:37.268
[Laughs]

24:37.303 --> 24:40.064
Is it weird
that I'm nervous right now?

24:40.099 --> 24:41.583
A little.

24:41.618 --> 24:43.965
I'm kidding,
it's totally normal.

24:43.999 --> 24:47.969
Hair is important, you know,
maybe the most important.

24:48.003 --> 24:50.937
It's gonna be great, though,
I promise.

25:31.702 --> 25:35.568
Oh, my God, Claire,
this is amazing.

25:35.603 --> 25:37.259
I seriously don't know
why you don't do weddings

25:37.294 --> 25:39.572
all of the time.
This is amazing!

25:39.607 --> 25:41.574
So much better
than the other girl.

25:41.609 --> 25:42.955
Here.

25:45.302 --> 25:47.235
Check it out from behind.

25:50.031 --> 25:51.377
Oh...

25:51.411 --> 25:52.792
[Chuckles]

25:52.827 --> 25:54.691
It's not that
I don't like to do weddings,

25:54.725 --> 25:56.037
I just...

25:56.071 --> 25:58.833
I don't know,
I find them really...

26:00.662 --> 26:02.215
Intense?

26:02.250 --> 26:04.217
Yeah. [Chuckles]

26:06.634 --> 26:07.842
Wow.

26:07.876 --> 26:09.637
Uh! Can't wait to see this
with the dress.

26:09.671 --> 26:11.293
Oh. Neither can I.

26:11.328 --> 26:13.295
- Can you send me a photo?
- Oh, yeah.

26:13.330 --> 26:16.298
Make sure you take it down
before Charlie sees it.

26:16.333 --> 26:18.059
How much do I owe you?

26:18.093 --> 26:20.958
- 65?
- Oh, that's a steal.

26:26.723 --> 26:29.242
I wish I had someone
to show it to tonight.

26:32.452 --> 26:34.385
Hey, what are you doing
tonight?

26:34.420 --> 26:37.872
You wanna come over and see
the hair and dress together?

26:39.218 --> 26:41.703
- I... I'd be happy to.
- Yeah?

26:41.738 --> 26:43.222
Cool, I'll text you
my address.

26:43.256 --> 26:46.259
Oh, I...
I'd appreciate that.

26:46.294 --> 26:50.367
- Like, uh... maybe eat dinner?
- Sure, but what about Charlie?

26:50.401 --> 26:54.129
Oh, he'll probably be working
late, so... girl's night. Yeah?

26:54.164 --> 26:56.684
- Yeah.
- Great. I love it!

26:56.718 --> 26:57.926
Alright, see you tonight.

26:57.961 --> 26:59.341
Yeah.

27:14.356 --> 27:16.048
[Chuckles]

27:35.067 --> 27:37.000
[Car door slams]

28:02.542 --> 28:04.890
Hey, come on in!

28:05.925 --> 28:07.962
Sorry, it's a mess in here.

28:08.859 --> 28:10.205
Ugh! I know.

28:10.240 --> 28:12.311
I told him I didn't want it,
yet here it is.

28:12.345 --> 28:14.244
I already feel like
I'm running in place all day

28:14.278 --> 28:15.763
at work, you know?

28:15.797 --> 28:17.247
So, when I run, I actually
want to get somewhere.

28:17.281 --> 28:18.386
You know what I'm saying?

28:18.420 --> 28:19.767
Oh, I was starving,

28:19.801 --> 28:21.769
so I ordered pizza.
I hope that's cool.

28:22.562 --> 28:24.150
Sounds great.

28:28.948 --> 28:32.262
Oh, this is great.

28:32.296 --> 28:34.264
It's Merlot.
I hope that's OK.

28:34.298 --> 28:36.818
Yes.
Always yes.

28:38.440 --> 28:39.994
[Cork pops]

28:40.960 --> 28:43.204
[Wine pouring]

28:48.002 --> 28:49.313
Oh.

28:49.348 --> 28:53.179
To Claire,
the savior of my wedding.

28:53.214 --> 28:55.216
- Oh, I'm sorry.
- No. No big deal.

28:55.250 --> 28:56.769
Do you want to see this dress?

28:58.150 --> 28:59.220
Of course.

29:00.014 --> 29:01.187
I'll be right back.

29:57.865 --> 30:00.419
Hey, Claire, could you come
up here and help me with this?

30:00.453 --> 30:02.317
Yeah, coming.

30:15.330 --> 30:17.850
[♪ Music playing faintly]

30:21.026 --> 30:22.268
[Knocking on door]

30:22.303 --> 30:25.030
- Ready?
- Yeah, come on in.

30:25.064 --> 30:28.965
Apparently, you can't put on
a wedding dress by yourself.

30:28.999 --> 30:31.312
Fucking buttons,
are you kidding me?

30:46.258 --> 30:47.431
Perfect.

30:47.466 --> 30:50.503
No.
The hair is perfect.

30:50.538 --> 30:52.574
Seriously, Claire,
it's amazing.

30:52.609 --> 30:55.370
I owe you so, so much.

30:55.405 --> 30:56.889
I'm just glad you like it.

30:58.304 --> 31:00.444
Oh, can you take some photos
for my mom and sister?

31:00.479 --> 31:01.514
Yeah, of course.

31:04.724 --> 31:06.243
OK.

31:08.107 --> 31:09.660
- Ready?
- Yeah.

31:15.252 --> 31:17.013
[Both chuckling]

31:17.047 --> 31:18.014
OK.

31:18.048 --> 31:19.429
- And the back, too?
- Yeah.

31:26.263 --> 31:27.540
OK, got it.

31:27.575 --> 31:29.301
Thank you.

31:29.335 --> 31:31.165
And do you mind helping me
get this off

31:31.199 --> 31:33.132
before I mess it up?

31:56.190 --> 31:57.985
There you go.

31:58.019 --> 32:00.711
- I'm gonna wait downstairs.
- OK.

32:10.583 --> 32:14.553
I never even thought
I'd be a bride.

32:14.587 --> 32:18.039
I always thought if I got
married, it would be on a whim.

32:18.074 --> 32:20.524
- Really?
- Yeah.

32:20.559 --> 32:23.424
I was super rebellious
in high school.

32:23.458 --> 32:26.323
You know,
"Fuck the patriarchy."

32:26.358 --> 32:29.050
- I went to my prom in a tux.
- [Both chuckle]

32:29.085 --> 32:31.190
- I wouldn't have guessed that.
- Yeah.

32:32.226 --> 32:33.468
Oh!

32:33.503 --> 32:36.506
Hopefully, younger me
doesn't hate current me.

32:41.235 --> 32:44.203
It looks like
you have a huge family.

32:44.238 --> 32:46.102
Yeah.

32:46.136 --> 32:49.588
They take up like half
of the wedding invitations.

32:49.622 --> 32:52.971
Oh, shit. See, the younger me
does hate current me.

32:53.592 --> 32:56.008
It's nice...

32:56.043 --> 32:57.803
that you're close
to your family.

32:57.837 --> 32:59.356
Mm.

33:03.843 --> 33:06.398
Is that your mom
in that picture?

33:06.432 --> 33:08.296
Yeah.

33:08.331 --> 33:10.264
And your dad?

33:10.298 --> 33:12.024
Uh... no.

33:12.059 --> 33:15.476
That is my uncle.
My mom's brother.

33:15.510 --> 33:17.443
My dad wasn't around.

33:17.478 --> 33:19.307
Really?

33:19.342 --> 33:21.309
Yeah.

33:21.344 --> 33:24.347
He was one of those classy gents
who promised everything

33:24.381 --> 33:27.350
and then took off
once the baby was born.

33:27.384 --> 33:28.799
I never knew him.

33:30.732 --> 33:33.321
Let's just say I'm walking
myself down the aisle.

33:34.564 --> 33:37.325
Oh, God, listen to me.

33:37.360 --> 33:40.570
Getting married turns you
into such a narcissist.

33:40.604 --> 33:42.365
It's like me, me, me.
Stories about me.

33:42.399 --> 33:44.056
Tell me about you, Claire.

33:44.091 --> 33:46.783
What about you,
are you close to your family?

33:48.509 --> 33:50.166
Oh, um...

33:54.446 --> 33:56.862
I never knew my dad either.

33:56.896 --> 33:58.415
Oh.

33:59.692 --> 34:01.384
I'm sorry.

34:03.110 --> 34:05.250
Oh, don't let it get to you.

34:07.666 --> 34:09.668
It's not you, it's him.

34:12.291 --> 34:14.673
I mean, look how amazing
we turned out.

34:15.605 --> 34:17.193
Fuck him.

34:19.505 --> 34:21.197
What about your mom?

34:23.889 --> 34:26.340
She died when I was 17.

34:27.548 --> 34:30.378
Oh, Jesus, I'm sorry.

34:35.866 --> 34:37.696
This is her.

34:37.730 --> 34:39.767
She was only 35.

34:42.149 --> 34:44.358
She's really beautiful.

34:44.392 --> 34:46.118
She was drunk.

34:47.223 --> 34:48.707
I mean...

34:49.639 --> 34:51.675
that's how she died.

34:55.817 --> 34:59.131
She was a hair stylist also.

34:59.166 --> 35:03.377
She was always changing her
hair color and her hair style.

35:03.411 --> 35:06.380
She never kept it the same way
for more than a few months.

35:08.382 --> 35:11.178
I never knew
who was gonna come home.

35:14.836 --> 35:17.184
Well...

